{"questionId":"9067971","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Chlorine undergoes many reactions.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Chlorine gas reacts with water to produce hypochlorous acid and hydrochloric acid.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math class=\"wrs_chemistry\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>Cl</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo> </mo><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>+</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mo> </mo><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>⇌</mo><mi>HClO</mi><mo> </mo><mo>(</mo><mi>aq</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>+</mo><mi>HCl</mi><mo> </mo><mo>(</mo><mi>aq</mi><mo>)</mo></math></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Calculate the concentration of </span><math class=\"wrs_chemistry\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mo>+</mo></msup><mo> </mo><mo>(</mo><mi>aq</mi><mo>)</mo></math><span class=\"fontstyle0\">&nbsp;in a </span><math class=\"wrs_chemistry\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>HClO</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mi>aq</mi></mfenced></math><span class=\"fontstyle0\"> solution with a </span><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" class=\"wrs_chemistry\"><mi>pH</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>61</mn></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math class=\"wrs_chemistry\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>«</mo><mo>[</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mo>+</mo></msup><mo>]</mo><mo>=</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>61</mn></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mo>»</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></msup><mo> </mo><mo>«</mo><mi>mol</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mi>dm</mi><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><mo>»</mo></math>&nbsp;✔</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9067971","referenceCode":"20N.2.sl.TZ0.c(iii)","subject